Key Match Events: Andrew Wiggins exploded in the third quarter, tallying 18 points in the third quarter on 8-of-7 shooting from the field with three made 3-pointers.
Dennis Schroder notched his highest-scoring performance as a Warrior, scoring 17 points on 6-of-15 shooting from the field to go along with nine assists and three rebounds in 36 minutes.
Pre-Game Insights: The Golden State Warriors were shorthanded with Steph Curry, Brandin Podziemski and Gary Payton II all sidelined.
Jonathan Kuminga exited the game with an ankle injury late in the second quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: The Warriors finished with 121-113 against the Grizzlies, riding a two-game winning streak to start 2025.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Six different members of the Warriors tallied 11 or more points against the Grizzlies.
The game took place at Chase Center.
